31:03.480 --> 31:04.480
And I think that's one of the challenges.

31:04.480 --> 31:05.640
So we're faced with these averages.

31:05.640 --> 31:11.600
We have to take 10,000 sperm or a million and sort of infer what's happening.

31:11.600 --> 31:18.080
And the only way to get experimentally at this process involves embryo transfer and

31:18.080 --> 31:23.800
vitro fertilization, which are all very artificial in their process and how that

31:23.800 --> 31:26.440
epigenetic effects in it of themselves.

31:26.440 --> 31:30.720
So this is one of the issues that we come across when we do these studies in the lab.

31:30.720 --> 31:33.840
We can show it through embryo transfer.

31:33.840 --> 31:40.200
But you've done something that's completely unrelated to the natural process of reproduction

31:40.200 --> 31:42.720
and whether it's relevant.

31:42.720 --> 31:50.760
I think that you can kind of expand that kind of concern to, okay, perhaps we would be able

31:50.760 --> 31:57.000
to show epigenetic inheritance in the lab in species that are short-lived.

31:57.000 --> 32:03.520
But would it be relevant on a wide-scale process, you know, in society, in natural environments

32:03.520 --> 32:08.160
where you have long-lived species that need to adapt to changing environments all the

32:08.160 --> 32:09.160
time.

32:09.160 --> 32:14.600
So when people start talking about epigenetic inheritance in response to the quality of

32:14.600 --> 32:19.360
the social environment, I thought, well, why would you want your social environment to

32:19.360 --> 32:21.640
be inherited through your germline?

32:21.640 --> 32:24.960
That seems nonsensical in terms of adaptation.

32:24.960 --> 32:30.400
You should respond to the social environment which you're in and adapt accordingly because

32:30.400 --> 32:34.160
that's the best predictor of the world that you live in.

32:34.160 --> 32:40.960
But I still think it's possible, but I think we need to think about whether these would

32:40.960 --> 32:44.080
actually play out in the real world.

32:44.080 --> 32:47.560
When you say social environment, I mean, I'm a molecular biologist.

32:47.560 --> 32:49.640
