32:49.640 --> 32:56.320
Anything from the quality of mother-infant interactions to peer interactions to, you

32:56.320 --> 33:02.360
know, adults' social interactions, so whether you're socially isolated or interacting with

33:02.360 --> 33:03.360
groups.

33:03.360 --> 33:09.200
The problem, I guess, is that you can never separate social interactions from stress reactivity.

33:09.200 --> 33:12.520
And so stress may be transducing the information.

33:12.520 --> 33:16.960
Certainly we think in the case of mother-infant interactions, it's not that, let's say, that

33:16.960 --> 33:23.440
the pure sociality of it, but rather the physical aspects of mother-infant interactions that

33:23.440 --> 33:26.480
are transducing the epigenetic marks.

33:26.480 --> 33:33.000
So are you saying that social interactions of a mother can affect the social interactions

33:33.000 --> 33:34.000
of the offspring?

