33:54.640 --> 33:57.080
So in, I work in rodents, right?

33:57.080 --> 33:59.920
So we have control over nature.

33:59.920 --> 34:02.360
Everyone's got the same genome.

34:02.360 --> 34:03.360
But yes.

34:03.360 --> 34:09.040
So the issue, and I think this is really important in the context of these discussions, is that

34:09.040 --> 34:11.880
in humans you have genetic variation.

34:11.880 --> 34:16.200
And you have a lot of what can be called many things, but niche selection.

34:16.200 --> 34:22.320
So people find themselves in environments because of biological drives that may be driven by

34:22.320 --> 34:24.040
DNA sequence.

34:24.040 --> 34:28.000
So it is almost impossible to separate out these questions.

34:28.000 --> 34:33.400
There's some really interesting work now in humans, now that artificial reproductive

34:33.400 --> 34:39.120
technology is so widespread in its use to look at egg donors and embryo transfer and

34:39.120 --> 34:44.240
all, you know, where mothers are caring offspring that are not genetically related to them and

34:44.240 --> 34:45.600
all these various combinations.

34:45.600 --> 34:53.160
And it does suggest that there are some later life characteristics, psychiatric illnesses

34:53.160 --> 34:58.520
that are driven by, you know, matches or mismatches between the genetic characteristics of the

34:58.520 --> 35:04.960
mother and genetic characteristics of the offspring or something about the in utero environment.

35:04.960 --> 35:13.160
A lot of the studies now that are focused on human analyses of epigenetics really are

35:13.160 --> 35:17.920
highlighting that you need to look at both the genetic variation and epigenetic variation

35:17.920 --> 35:18.920
together.

35:18.920 --> 35:21.080
So they're not separate entities.

35:21.080 --> 35:25.360
Only in the lab we treat them like that, but we're working with organisms that don't have

35:25.360 --> 35:26.600
genetic variability.

35:26.600 --> 35:32.120
But there are gene environment interactions at the level of epigenetic changes is, you

35:32.120 --> 35:33.120
know, widespread.

35:33.120 --> 35:39.640
