36:42.160 --> 36:48.160
But you know, then I think we get more into kind of theoretical philosophical musings

36:48.160 --> 36:52.760
about how this plays out in evolution.

36:52.760 --> 36:58.080
Certainly there's some suggestion that, you know, we're talking about retrotransposons.

36:58.080 --> 37:04.880
Areas of epigenetic variability or, you know, or stability may be areas where there's also

37:04.880 --> 37:07.040
likelihood of genetic variation.

37:07.040 --> 37:12.520
So, you know, there may be a process where if there's a lot of epigenetic variation going

37:12.520 --> 37:19.480
on, you know, between or within generations perhaps that will stabilize into the genome

37:19.480 --> 37:23.000
somehow through genetic variation.

37:23.000 --> 37:24.880
But I don't have a lot of strong views on it.

37:24.880 --> 37:31.080
I think it doesn't have to play out in evolution in the way that genes do.

37:31.080 --> 37:37.000
I think it should be its own entity as it should be within the discussions of inheritance.

37:37.000 --> 37:45.240
So I'm more of an inclusive inheritance thinker when it comes to the term and the mechanisms

37:45.240 --> 37:46.240
of inheritance.

37:46.240 --> 37:51.880
We can transmit information in a number of ways through social, through parental effects,

37:51.880 --> 37:54.200
through genes, through epigenetics.

37:54.200 --> 37:58.360
They're all different mechanisms working together to confer inheritance.

37:58.360 --> 38:04.000
But of course inheritance is just a mechanism that's important for the evolutionary process.

38:04.000 --> 38:05.960
It's not the only one.

38:05.960 --> 38:11.120
I'd like to add to that that I think, you know, if, you know, the standard image of

38:11.120 --> 38:17.000
Lamarckian inheritance is this, you know, pseudo giraffe animal that isn't yet a giraffe,

38:17.000 --> 38:20.480
and then the giraffe stretches, tries to stretch its neck.

38:20.480 --> 38:26.880
And then over time its efforts to change itself, you know, have resulted in changing its genome.

38:26.880 --> 38:32.040
And I think, you know, we have to be careful to think that, you know, anything could, you

38:32.040 --> 38:36.480
know, let's assume for a moment that epigenetic inheritance does exist, all right?

38:36.480 --> 38:40.560
