41:05.400 --> 41:12.040
And what was being propagated had to confer some sort of adaptation to the individual inheriting.

41:12.040 --> 41:18.480
So, you know, and we don't use any of those criteria when we're testing these hypothesis.

41:18.480 --> 41:24.640
And also, when it comes to Lamarck, the prevailing theory of inheritance at the time was pangenesis,

41:24.640 --> 41:28.880
which was this idea that little particles of every cell in your body would break off

41:28.880 --> 41:32.360
into your gametes and be transmitted directly to offspring.

41:32.360 --> 41:38.680
Now, maybe microRNA are a good, you know, part of that story reemerging.

41:38.680 --> 41:42.280
But it's certainly a very different way of thinking about inheritance in general than

41:42.280 --> 41:43.280
we do now.

41:43.280 --> 41:48.760
And I think, you know, I think there's room for Lamarckian ideas.

41:48.760 --> 41:53.680
At least epigenetics provide a potential mechanism for all the marks, the theory.

